title: The Sayings of Confucius
creator: Confucius
description:
LibriVox recording of The Sayings of Confucius, in the public domain.
The LibriVox catalog page for this work lists the LibriVox readers. Promoting virtues such as filial devotion, compassion, loyalty, and propriety, these dialogues between the ancient Chinese philosopher Confucius and his disciples comprise the crux of Confucianism. (Summary by Andrea L). For more information on LibriVox, or to volunteer, please see: http://librivox.org/
